female male PN female male PN female male PN Venter (
Fig. 2
). Slit between peritrematal shield and body margin relatively narrow. Posterior ends of peritrematal shield truncated, straight, reaching beyond the level of R 1 . Peritremes straight, with curved anterior section. One pair of narrow post-genital sclerites present. Anterior margin of ventri-anal shield with two pairs of setae. Pre-anal setae short simple, post-anal seta elongate, distally pilose. Ventri-anal pores situated anterolateral to adanal setae. Sternal shield with reticulate ornamentation, ventri-anal shield covered by squamous pattern.

Larva (
Fig. 6
). Length of idiosoma 208–230 μm (mean 220 ); width 170–182 μm (mean 178 ) (n = 4 ). Podonotal setae elongate, densely plumose. Opisthonotal setae J 2 , J 3 , J 5 , Z 2 and S 2 short and simple, others elongate, densely plumose. Well-sclerotised parts of dorsal idiosoma with a reticulate pattern, surface of opisthonotum covered by small cavities lying at intersections of a reticulate ornamentation. Dorsal cavities situated in a row, the medial pair fused.
